$MP  Those who have followed my charting for a while are maybe thinking "Troutter has change, do breakout trades not work?" For years I'd been posting breakout setups and suddenly now I'm posting more bounce plays.  For many years the markets were mostly bullish, so breakout plays worked just fine.  Then the bear market struck and many stocks are still trying to find their footing. Which has made making money from the bull side more challenging.  Traders who are ok with trying to fight the trend and are looking for low risk/high reward setups may want to take a closer look at MP.  Granted, when the risk is low and the reward is high the probability of success is also low.  You'll never get high probability and high reward to risk together.  It just doesn't work that way, but many times that's ok when the reward/risk is also high, like in this example it's about 4:1. There's always a bull case and there's always a bear case.  Who wins next is yet to be determined. Happy trading  $STUDY
